    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-11-20T19:27:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-11-20T19:27:00-05:00" n="656"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d656">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">762.022/11–2053: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 656<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Office of the United States High Commissioner for
                            Germany</gloss>, at Bonn</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d656fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MDII1"
                            >MacArthur</persName> and cleared with Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-11-20T19:27:00-05:00"
                            >November 20, 1953—7:27 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1592. Eyes only. For Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_CJP1">Conant</persName>
                    from the Secretary. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 1510.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d656fn2">Telegram 1510 reported that Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> would communicate with <persName
                            corresp="#p_CJP1">Conant</persName> in the next several days regarding
                        the need to obtain a definitive statement from <persName corresp="#p_AK1"
                            >Adenauer</persName> on the Saar and the <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                            >EDC</gloss>. (123 <persName corresp="#p_CJP1">Conant, James
                            B.</persName>)</note> 1. I am writing you by air pouch giving my views
                    with respect to Saar and <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> and I am enclosing
                    a personal letter from me to <persName corresp="#p_AK1">Adenauer</persName>,
                    which, unless you perceive objection, you should deliver to him.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d656fn3">For <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>’ letters
                        to <persName corresp="#p_CJP1">Conant</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_AK1">Adenauer</persName>, see <ref target="#d657">
                            <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>
                        </ref> and <ref target="#d658">Document 658</ref>.</note> In brief my letter
                    to <persName corresp="#p_AK1">Adenauer</persName> sets forth our conviction that
                    an early Saar settlement is essential; that our policy with respect to Europe is
                    not based on France or Germany but on Franco-German unity and cooperation; and
                    that <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> remains a most fundamental objective of
                    US foreign policy.</p>
                <p>2. I understand that <persName corresp="#p_AK1">Adenauer</persName> may
                    contemplate sending <persName corresp="#p_HW1">Hallstein</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_GE1">Gerstenmaier</persName> to U.S. to discuss Saar
                    and <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss>. Should he approach you about such a
                    trip please let me know at once. Although I believe my letter to you with
                    enclosure to <persName corresp="#p_AK1">Adenauer</persName> indicates clearly
                    U.S. view, there might be some advantage in my stating them directly to
                        <persName corresp="#p_HW1">Hallstein</persName> and I would of course wish
                    your recommendation on this before making a decision. <gloss target="#t_FYI1"
                        >FYI</gloss> I would not be able to see <persName corresp="#p_HW1"
                        >Hallstein</persName> here during the period December 4–8 when I will be in
                    Bermuda and I will be leaving for Paris <gloss target="#t_NAC2">NAC</gloss>
                    meeting evening December 11, departing Paris for Washington December 17.<note
                        n="4" xml:id="d656fn4">For documentation on the Bermuda Conference, see <ref
                            target="frus1952-54v05p2#pg_1710">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, Part
                            2, pp. 1710</ref> ff. For documentation on the Twelfth Session of the
                        North Atlantic Council, Dec. 14–16, see <ref
                            target="frus1952-54v05p1#pg_454">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>., Part 1, pp. 454</ref> ff.</note> If it
                    were deemed desirable I could of course see him in Washington <pb facs="0274"
                        n="1474" xml:id="pg_1474"/> before or immediately after Bermuda or in Paris
                    during <gloss target="#t_NAC2">NAC</gloss> meeting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
